  "name": "activity_brake",
  "description": "Activity-dependent suppression via negative feedback. 4 RS sensor neurons integrate weak excitatory input from monitored populations. When enough sensors fire, they drive 2 FS suppressor neurons that output strong inhibitory bursts. Implements 'volume knob' — high activity triggers suppression, low activity releases it. Gap junction between suppressors ensures coordinated output. Self-excitation on suppressors extends burst duration for effective calming. Pattern: thalamic reticular nucleus / inhibitory interneuron pools.",
